    "monster5949": "<h1 class=monster>Unhallowed Wight<br><span class=type>Medium natural humanoid (undead)</span><br><span class=level>Level 7 Soldier<span class=xp> XP 300</span></span></h1><table class=bodytable><tr><td><b>HP</b> 80; <b>Bloodied</b> 40<td class=rightalign><b>Initiative</b> +5<tr><td><b>AC</b> 23, <b>Fortitude</b> 20, <b>Reflex</b> 15, <b>Will</b> 19<td class=rightalign><b>Perception</b>+2<tr><td><b>Speed</b> 6, climb 4<td class=rightalign>Darkvision<tr><td colspan=2><b>Immune</b> disease, poison; <b>Resist</b> 10 necrotic; <b>Vulnerable</b> 5 radiant<tr><td colspan=2></table><h2>Standard Actions</h2><p class='flavor alt'>(⚔) <b>Soul-Draining Claw</b> (necrotic) ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Attack:</i> Melee 1 (one creature); +12 vs. AC</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Hit:</i> 1d8 + 5 necrotic damage, and the target loses a healing surge and is immobilized (save ends).</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Special:</i> If the wight takes radiant damage, this attack does not cause targets to lose a healing surge until the end of the wight's next turn.</p><h2>Triggered Actions</h2><p class='flavor alt'>ᗕ <b>Unhallowed Blight</b> (necrotic) ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Trigger:</i> An enemy within 5 squares makes a successful saving throw.</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Attack (Opportunity Action):</i> Close burst 5 (triggering enemy in the burst); +10 vs. Fortitude</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Hit:</i> 5 necrotic damage, and the target grants combat advantage until the end of its next turn.</p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Skills</b> Athletics +12, Intimidate +11<br> <b>Str</b> 19 (+7)                <b>Dex</b> 11 (+3)                <b>Wis</b> 8 (+2)<br><b>Con</b> 16 (+6)                <b>Int</b> 10 (+3)                <b>Cha</b> 17 (+6)</p><p class=flavor><b>Alignment</b> Evil       <b> Languages</b> Common</p><p class=publishedIn>Published in Neverwinter Campaign Setting, page(s) 109, Dungeon Magazine 218.</p>",
    "monster6609": "<h1 class=monster>Young Avalanche Dragon<br><span class=type>Large elemental magical beast (dragon, earth)</span><br><span class=level>Level 7 Elite Skirmisher<span class=xp> XP 600</span></span></h1><table class=bodytable><tr><td><b>HP</b> 164; <b>Bloodied</b> 82<td class=rightalign><b>Initiative</b> +9<tr><td><b>AC</b> 21, <b>Fortitude</b> 20, <b>Reflex</b> 19, <b>Will</b> 18<td class=rightalign><b>Perception</b>+6<tr><td><b>Speed</b> 7 (earth walk), fly 7<td class=rightalign>Darkvision, tremorsense 5<tr><td colspan=2><b>Saving Throws</b> +2; <b>Action Points</b> 1</table><h2>Traits</h2><p class='flavor alt'>☼ <b>Rain of Stone</b> ✦ <b>Aura</b> 1</p><p class=flavorIndent>Any enemy that ends its turn in the aura takes 5 damage.</p><p class='flavor alt'> <b>Landslide</b> </p><p class=flavorIndent>Being slowed affects only the dragon's fly speed.</p><h2>Standard Actions</h2><p class='flavor alt'>(⚔) <b>Claw</b> ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Attack:</i> Melee 2 (one creature); +12 vs. AC</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Hit:</i> 2d6 + 8 damage, and the target falls prone.</p><p class='flavor alt'>⚔ <b>Avalanche Trample</b> ✦ <b>At-Will</b></p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Effect:</i> The dragon moves up to its speed, and it can move through enemies' spaces. If an enemy within 2 squares of the dragon hits it with an attack during this movement, the dragon uses claw against that enemy. Each time the dragon enters an enemy's space for the first time during this movement, it uses claw against that enemy.</p><h2>Minor Actions</h2><p class='flavor alt'>ᗕ <b>Blinding Dust</b> (zone) ✦ <b>Recharge</b> when first bloodied</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Effect:</i> Close burst 2; the burst creates a zone that lasts until the end of the dragon's next turn. The zone is heavily obscured.</p><p class='flavor alt'> <b>Expanding Aura</b> ✦ <b>Recharge</b> when the dragon starts its turn and its rain of stone is smaller than aura 5 </p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Effect:</i> The rain of stone aura expands by 2 squares.</p><p class='flavor alt'>ᗕ <b>Smashing Stone</b> ✦ <b>Recharge</b> when the dragon starts its turn and its rain of stone is aura 5</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Attack:</i> Close burst 5 (enemies in the burst); +10 vs. Reflex</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Hit:</i> 1d6 + 7 damage, and the target falls prone. The target also takes ongoing 5 damage and cannot stand up (save ends both).</p><p class=flavorIndent><i>Effect:</i> The dragon's rain of stone reverts to aura 1.</p><p class='flavor alt'><b>Str</b> 20 (+8)                <b>Dex</b> 18 (+7)                <b>Wis</b> 17 (+6)<br><b>Con</b> 18 (+7)                <b>Int</b> 15 (+5)                <b>Cha</b> 17 (+6)</p><p class=flavor><b>Alignment</b> Unaligned       <b> Languages</b> Common, Draconic, Primordial</p><p class=publishedIn>Published in Dragon Magazine 424.</p>",
